The paper proposes a novel semantic tagging task for multilingual semantic parsing and presents a tagger using deep residual networks. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically semantic and Part-of-Speech (POS) tagging, which are typically categorized under cs.CL. The use of deep residual networks also suggests a focus on machine learning and neural networks, which are commonly categorized under cs.LG and cs.AI. Additionally, the use of character representations and auxiliary loss functions may suggest a focus on neural language models, which are commonly categorized under cs.NE. Finally, the use of ResNets may also suggest a focus on computer vision, which is commonly categorized under cs.CV.
